cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing D2D communications using UAV relays, which falls under the networking and internet architecture domain. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing the available bandwidth and power allocations of the D2D links, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an optimization model for multiple UAVs working as relays, which involves control and system theory. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The heuristic algorithm used for optimizing the UAVs' trajectory and UAV-user associations can be considered as an AI technique. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with robotics, the use of UAVs as relays can be considered as a robotic application.
